---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms and Conditions — TT Motorcycle School"
  description="Terms and conditions for training at TT Motorcycle School. Please read before booking."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__sub">
        Please read the following terms carefully before booking or attending
        training with TT Motorcycle School.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose tc-prose">
        <h2>Pupil Documentation</h2>
        <p>
          The following are Driving and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA)
          regulations and must be adhered to at all times on all courses.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            It is the pupil's responsibility to ensure that all necessary and
            relevant documentation is valid and carried throughout training:
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>CBT</strong> — a valid <strong>UK</strong> provisional or
                full driving licence.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong
                  >A1 / A2 / Direct Access licence training or practical test</strong
                > — a valid <strong>UK</strong> provisional or full driving licence,
                a valid CBT certificate, and a valid Motorcycle Theory Test certificate.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Advanced &amp; Back to Biking</strong> — a valid full <strong
                  >UK</strong
                > driving licence.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            If the pupil does not provide the necessary documentation or fails
            the eyesight check (reading a vehicle registration plate at 20.5
            metres / 67 ft, with or without optical aids), the deposit will be
            forfeited and training will not commence.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Pupil's Clothing</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            It is the pupil's responsibility to wear suitable sturdy clothing
            when undertaking motorcycle training — sturdy footwear (not steel
            toe-cap boots or shoes) and preferably sturdy trousers (denim or
            leather). A jacket, helmet, gloves, hi-viz, and waterproofs will be
            supplied if necessary.
          </li>
          <li>
            If a pupil arrives wearing inappropriate clothing, TT Motorcycle
            School reserves the right to cancel training without refund.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Medical Conditions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            It is the pupil's responsibility to inform TT Motorcycle School of
            any medical conditions at the time of booking. Failure to do so may
            result in cancellation of training.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Reading the Highway Code</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong
              >It is essential that all pupils read and understand the Highway
              Code before attending any motorcycle training.</strong
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Before booking, you must consider that to undertake any course you
            need to be able to converse in basic English. You <strong
              >must</strong
            > be able to understand your instructor, and they must be able to understand
            you. Safety is our priority and full communication is essential. If you
            cannot meet this condition, no training will go ahead and you will lose
            your fees.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Damage, Loss &amp; Insurance</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            TT Motorcycle School does not provide insurance to cover illness,
            personal injury, or unplanned course cancellation.
          </li>
          <li>
            TT Motorcycle School advises pupils to make their own arrangements
            in relation to the above if they feel it necessary.
          </li>
          <li>
            Whilst training, pupils are insured under a full comprehensive
            insurance policy provided by TT Motorcycle School.
          </li>
          <li>
            In the event of a pupil causing damage to vehicles provided by TT
            Motorcycle School, the following voluntary excess charges apply:
            <ul>
              <li>Moped — £350.00</li>
              <li>Up to 125cc — £500.00</li>
              <li>500cc and above — £1,000.00</li>
            </ul>
            A full price list of damaged or lost items will be provided to the pupil
            on request.
          </li>
          <li>
            If any pupil fails to follow instructions given whilst training,
            resulting in an incident or accident where the pupil has become
            separated from the instructor, the insurance policy may be
            invalidated and the pupil will be liable for <strong
              >all costs</strong
            > in the full recovery and repair of the vehicle.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Alcohol &amp; Drugs</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong
              >If a pupil is considered to be under the influence of alcohol or
              drugs (whether prescribed or not), TT Motorcycle School reserves
              the right to cancel training without refund.</strong
            >
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Tiredness &amp; Fatigue</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            It is the pupil's responsibility to ensure they are capable of
            remaining awake and alert throughout training. It is not advised to
            participate in motorcycle training without adequate sleep.
          </li>
          <li>
            If the pupil is considered too tired due to lack of sleep or any
            other reason, TT Motorcycle School reserves the right to postpone or
            cancel training.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Training Standards</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>All training is provided at the discretion of the school.</li>
          <li>
            Where possible the pupil will be kept on the same machine throughout
            their course, but this is not guaranteed.
          </li>
          <li>
            TT Motorcycle School reserves the right to halt or offer alternative
            training if a pupil is deemed a hazard to themselves or any member
            of the public. Any refund, partial or full, is at the instructor's
            discretion.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Payments &amp; Cancellations</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            A non-refundable deposit must be paid prior to confirmation of any
            A1 / A2 / Direct Access / Back to Biking / Advanced training course.
          </li>
          <li>
            CBT bookings will only be confirmed with payment in full at the time
            of booking.
          </li>
          <li>
            Full payment for A1, A2, Direct Access, Back to Biking, and Advanced
            training courses must be made at least 14 days prior to the first
            day of training.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Strict Cancellation Policy</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Pupils must arrive on time. Late arrivals will be excluded from the
            course without refund, and any re-booking will be subject to an
            additional fee.
          </li>
          <li>
            If a pupil cancels a CBT or A1 / A2 / Direct Access / Refresher
            course giving 14 working days' notice, a full refund will be made <strong
              >minus</strong
            > the non-refundable deposit (if paid).
          </li>
          <li>
            If a pupil cancels any training without giving 14 working days'
            notice, the full course payment (and deposit if paid) will be
            retained.
          </li>
          <li>
            If the pupil fails to arrive on the day of any training without
            appropriate notice, the full amount for the day will be forfeited.
          </li>
          <li>
            If TT Motorcycle School cancels your course or any part thereof, an
            alternative date will be offered (see below for weather-related
            cancellations).
          </li>
          <li>
            TT Motorcycle School will not be held responsible for any DVSA test
            cancellations or failures.
          </li>
          <li>
            If weather conditions prevent CBT training from commencing, TT
            Motorcycle School will reschedule at no additional charge.
          </li>
          <li>
            If weather conditions require cancellation of A1, A2, Direct Access,
            Back to Biking, or Advanced training, alternative dates will be
            offered where possible.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Gift Vouchers</strong> — all vouchers are valid for 6 months from
            the date of issue and are only redeemable by the person named.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong
              >TT Motorcycle School operates a zero-tolerance policy on
              threatening or abusive behaviour in our workplace. We reserve the
              right to terminate a course without refund if we are subject to
              this behaviour. Any such instance will be reported to the
              appropriate authorities.</strong
            >
          </li>
        </ul>

        <hr />
        <p>
          For any questions regarding these terms, please <a href="/contact/"
            >contact us</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .tc-prose {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .tc-prose ul ul {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    list-style-type: disc;
  }

  .prose hr {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-block: var(--space-8);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
